╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 1.3: Find and Till                    ║
║  Category: Movement              Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  f <char>   Find next occurrence of char (lands ON the char)
  F <char>   Find previous occurrence of char
  t <char>   Till next occurrence of char (lands BEFORE the char)
  T <char>   Till previous occurrence of char
  Alt-.      Repeat the last f/t/F/T motion

NOTE: Unlike Vim, these work ACROSS LINES in Helix!

MNEMONIC: f=find (on it), t=till (before it)

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Each line has content between pipe | characters.
  Delete the content BETWEEN the pipes, keeping the pipes.

  Strategy:
  1. Move cursor to the first |
  2. Press  t |  to select till the next pipe (but not the pipe)
  3. Wait — that selects the | too. Instead: move one right with l
  4. Then  t |  to select up to (but not including) the next |
  5. Press  d  to delete

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

Keep |remove this part| and keep going.
Stay |delete everything in here| the end.
Before |this should be empty| after.
Hello |goodbye cruel world| friend.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

Keep || and keep going.
Stay || the end.
Before || after.
Hello || friend.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Position cursor on the first |, then press l to move
          one character right (onto the content to delete).
  Hint 2: Now press t | — this selects from cursor to just before
          the closing |.
  Hint 3: Press d to delete the selection. The pipes remain.
  Hint 4: Alternatively, use m i | (match inside vertical bars)
          which is covered in the text objects module. If you
          already know it, feel free to use it!
